This is a fork of a mirror of http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=1071

:BufOnly without an argument will unload all buffers but the current one.

:BufOnly with an argument will close all buffers but the supplied buffer name/number.

** EDITS **

I removed the aliases :Bonly :BOnly :Bufonly and left :BufOnly because the autocompletion gets annoying when there are multiple choices
